Privacy Policy
University of Limerick Hospitals Group built the NCHD at ULHG app as a Free app. This SERVICE is provided by University of Limerick Hospitals Group at no cost and is intended for use as is. This privacy policy describes how our company collects, uses and discloses your personal information and data when you use our services through our websites and/or application.
If you choose to use our Service, then you agree to the collection and use of information in relation to this policy. The Personal Information that we collect is used for providing and improving the Service. We will not use or share your information with anyone except as described in this Privacy Policy.
The terms used in this Privacy Policy have the same meanings as in our Terms and Conditions, which are accessible at NCHD at ULHG unless otherwise defined in this Privacy Policy.
What kind of data is collected?
For a better experience, while using our Service, we may require you to provide us with certain personally identifiable information, including but not limited to Account information including unique Account ID, mobile device or computer information and details, name, email address, job grade, localisation data, Data use and usage, IP address including connection logs and data, Navigator information including metadata, Diagnostic data or performance data, Any kind of other data voluntarily given by the User to GoodBarber or any other Third Party or entity, Login credentials (hashed), Other Personal Data relating to the individual data subject as set by the User. The information that we request will be retained by us and used as described in this privacy policy. Our company collects the following set of data and information:
How is the data collected?
You provide our company with most of the data we collect, we collect data and process personal data and information when:
You register online
Use our website or application when cookies are set on your device
Our company might also receive data and information indirectly from the following sources:​
